          <source>Azure Data Lake Storage Gen2 is easy to set up.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>It requires a <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>StorageV2 (General Purpose V2)<ept id="p1">**</ept> Azure Storage account with the Hierarchical namespace enabled.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Let's walk through an example of setting up an Data Lake Storage account in the Azure portal.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Sign in to the <bpt id="p1">[</bpt>Azure portal<ept id="p1">](https://portal.azure.com?azure-portal=true)</ept></source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Select <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Create a resource<ept id="p1">**</ept> and navigate to <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>Storage<ept id="p2">**</ept>.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Featured<ept id="p1">**</ept>, select <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>Storage account - blob, file, table, queue<ept id="p2">**</ept> as shown in the following screenshot.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Screenshot of the Azure portal showing the Create a resource, Storage account in highlights.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Next, in the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Create storage account<ept id="p1">**</ept> window, under the <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>Basics<ept id="p2">**</ept> tab, define a <bpt id="p3">**</bpt>storage account name<ept id="p3">**</ept>.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Set the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>location<ept id="p1">**</ept> to <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>Central US<ept id="p2">**</ept>.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Account kind<ept id="p1">**</ept> drop-down list, select <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>StorageV2 (general-purpose v2)<ept id="p2">**</ept> to create a Data Lake Storage Gen2 data store.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
